    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> finely (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped bacon</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the bacon is starting to crisp, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> to the pan with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Cook for 4 min or until the onion has softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> in 750ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the stock a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the risotto is cooking, line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> remaining bacon</strong> to the tray and drizzle over <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the bacon is well coated</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>asparagus</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add it to the tray with the bacon with a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>When the risotto has 10 min remaining, put the tray in the oven and cook for 12-15 min or until the bacon is crispy and the asparagus is tender \u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic glazed bacon</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>roasted asparagus</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the <strong>salad </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>remaining balsamic vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto<strong> </strong>is ready, stir through 3/4<strong> </strong>of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>bacon risotto</strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> balsamic glazed bacon & roasted asparagus </strong>with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> balsamic glazed bacon & asparagus topping</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/balsamic-glazed-bacon-and-roasted-asparagus-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> balsamic bacon & asparagus topping </strong>over the<strong> bacon risotto </strong>with the<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
